<br>
- You will only sponsor players that you have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>significant history</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with. Hunting with someone once in a pick-up group is hardly enough time to get to know someone.<br>
<br>
- Ask yourself “Is this someone I want to interact with in groups, in raids, and in guildchat every time I log on?” If you answer yes, then ask yourself “Is this someone my guildmates would want to interact with in groups, in raids, and in guildchat every time they log on?”<br>
<br>
- You are to provide the recruit sufficient information about our guild. You will explain the recruitment process as well as direct them to post on our message boards. <br>
<br>
- You will assist the recruit with meeting as many members as possible. You are responsible for making sure they join our chat channel and attend as many raids and hunts as they can.<br>
<br>
- Sponsorship does not end the day the recruit becomes a full member. As a sponsor, you effectively are underwriting that person for the entire duration of their membership. You will be asked to be involved in resolving any issues that may involve your recruit.<br>
